name: Amazon RDS Logs and Metrics
description: The Sumo Logic App for Amazon RDS Logs and Metrics provides visibility into your Amazon Relational Database Service (RDS) Metrics collected via a CloudWatch Metrics Source, and AWS CloudTrail API calls for RDS resources. The App’s Dashboards provide preconfigured searches and filters that allow you to monitor your RDS system's overview, CPU, memory, storage, network transmit and receive throughput, read and write operations, database connection count, disk queue depth, and CloudTrail Events (API calls).

panels.name: Use Filter (Top Right) to Filter by DB Identifier, Region, User, etc.
Geolocation of Events
panels.queryString:
$$Cloudtrail"rds.amazonaws.com"
| json "userIdentity.userName" as userName nodrop
| json "eventName","eventSource","userAgent","awsRegion","eventType","sourceIPAddress" nodrop
| json field=_raw "requestParameters.logFileName", "requestParameters.dBInstanceIdentifier", "requestParameters.numberOfLines" as logFileName,dBInstanceIdentifier,numberOfLines nodrop
| where eventSource matches "rds.amazonaws.com"
| lookup latitude, longitude, country_code, country_name, region, city, postal_code, area_code, metro_code from geo://default on ip=sourceIPAddress
| count by latitude, longitude, country_code, country_name, region, city, postal_code, area_code, metro_code
| sort _count

$$Cloudtrail"rds.amazonaws.com"
